<p>I would like to add a new item at the back of a list, and get the newly created item.</p>  <p>Let's assume that we could do something like this for one moment:</p>  <pre><code>class Temp {     public string First { get;set;}     public string Second { get;set;} } List&lt;string&gt; list = new List&lt;string&gt;(); var newItem = list.Push(); newItem.First="asd"; newItem.Second = "qwe; </code></pre>  <p>this would be easier than</p>  <pre><code>var newItem = new Temp(); newItem.First="asd"; newItem.Second = "qwe; list.Add(newItem); </code></pre>  <p><strong>especially when I can't use auto-properties.</strong></p>  <p>Is this possible?</p>